  "argv 就是个数组，遍历它用最普通的 for 循环：i 从 0 到 argc - 1。每个 argv[i] 是一个以 \\0 结尾的 C 字符串（char *），可以直接交给 printf 的 %s。最致命的错误是循环条件写成 i <= argc——这会访问 argv[argc]，那个位置是标准规定的 NULL 指针，对它解引用就是空指针崩溃。永远用 i < argc。": "argv is just an array, so walk it with an ordinary for loop: i from 0 to argc - 1. Each argv[i] is a \\0-terminated C string (char *) you can hand straight to printf's %s. The deadliest mistake is writing the condition as i <= argc — that touches argv[argc], which the standard guarantees is a NULL pointer, and dereferencing it is a null-pointer crash. Always use i < argc.",
