  "为什么从 argv[1] 开始数用户参数": "Why user arguments start at argv[1]",
  "很多新手在 ./tool hello 时纳闷「我只传了一个参数，为什么 argc 是 2」。因为 argv[0] 占用了第一个位置：它是你的程序被调用时的路径或名字。这其实很有用——程序可以靠它在错误信息里报出自己的名字（usage: ./tool ...）。但当你真正想处理「用户给的参数」时，几乎总是从 argv[1] 开始，并且用 argc - 1 来表示用户参数的个数。这条规则贯穿后面所有的校验与解析。": "Beginners running ./tool hello often wonder \"I passed one argument, why is argc 2?\" Because argv[0] occupies the first slot: it is the path or name your program was invoked with. That's actually useful — a program can use it to name itself in error messages (usage: ./tool ...). But when you genuinely want to process \"the arguments the user gave,\" you almost always start at argv[1] and treat argc - 1 as the number of user arguments. This rule runs through all the validation and parsing that follows.",
