  "第一道关：参数个数": "The first gate: argument count",
  "解析参数的第一步永远是「数对不对」。如果你的工具需要两个数字，用户却只给了一个，你应该立刻拒绝并告诉他怎么用——而不是去访问根本不存在的 argv[2]（那是越界读取）。记住程序名占掉 argv[0]，所以「需要两个用户参数」对应 argc == 3。判断写在最前面，个数不对就直接打用法、退出，后面的逻辑根本不必跑。这种「提前返回」让主逻辑保持干净。": "The first step in parsing arguments is always \"is the count right?\" If your tool needs two numbers but the user gives one, you must reject immediately and show how to use it — rather than touching a non-existent argv[2] (an out-of-bounds read). Remember the program name eats argv[0], so \"needs two user arguments\" corresponds to argc == 3. Put the check at the very top; if the count is wrong, print usage and exit, and the rest of the logic never runs. This early return keeps the main logic clean.",
