  "位置参数与选项": "Positional arguments and options",
  "命令行参数分两类。位置参数靠出现的顺序识别,比如 ./greet Allen 里的 Allen。选项(option/flag)以横杠开头,靠名字识别,跟顺序无关:--help、-v 这种。约定俗成单横杠跟短名(-h),双横杠跟长名(--help),一个功能通常两种都提供,方便手敲也方便写脚本。处理选项的核心动作就是:遍历 argv,逐个用字符串比较判断「这个词是不是我认识的某个选项」。": "Command-line arguments come in two kinds. Positional arguments are identified by their order, like Allen in ./greet Allen. Options (or flags) start with a dash and are identified by name regardless of order: --help, -v. By convention a single dash precedes a short name (-h) and a double dash a long name (--help), and one feature usually offers both for easy typing and easy scripting. The core action for handling options is: walk argv and, for each word, use string comparison to decide \"is this a flag I recognize?\"",
  "横杠开头的当选项，其余当位置参数": "Dash-prefixed words are options, the rest positionals",
  "选项可以乱序：-v Allen 和 Allen -v 都应该认出 -v，所以要遍历整个 argv 而不是只看固定位置。": "Options can appear in any order: both -v Allen and Allen -v should detect -v, so scan all of argv rather than fixed positions.",
  "字符串比较必须用 strcmp": "String comparison must use strcmp",
  "C 里最常见的坑之一:用 == 比较字符串。argv[i] == \"--help\" 比的是两个指针的地址,几乎永远为假,跟内容毫无关系。C 字符串是字符数组,比内容只能用 <string.h> 里的 strcmp:两个字符串相等时它返回 0(不是 1,记牢这个反直觉的约定)。所以判断写成 strcmp(argv[i], \"--help\") == 0。要同时认长短写法,用 || 连起来:既匹配 -h 也匹配 --help。": "One of C's most common traps: comparing strings with ==. argv[i] == \"--help\" compares two pointer addresses, is almost always false, and has nothing to do with the content. C strings are character arrays, and comparing content requires strcmp from <string.h>: it returns 0 when the two strings are equal (not 1 — burn that counterintuitive convention into memory). So the test reads strcmp(argv[i], \"--help\") == 0. To accept both forms, join them with ||: match -h as well as --help.",
  "strcmp 返回 0 表示相等": "strcmp returns 0 to mean equal",
  "strcmp 相等时返回 0，所以条件是 == 0；写成 if (strcmp(...)) 含义正好相反。": "strcmp returns 0 on equality, so the condition is == 0; writing if (strcmp(...)) means the exact opposite.",
  "--help 是正常路径，不是错误": "--help is a normal path, not an error",
  "一个容易做错的细节:用户主动敲 --help,是合法且预期的请求,不是出错。所以帮助文本应该打到 stdout(正常输出),并且 return 0(成功退出);而参数用错(比如缺参数)才打到 stderr 并 return 非零。把两者分清很重要——CI 脚本里 ./tool --help 如果意外返回非零,会被当成失败。同理,用一个标志变量(int verbose = 0)记录开关类选项的状态:遍历时遇到 -v 就置 1,遍历完再根据这个标志决定行为,而不是边遍历边做事。": "An easily-botched detail: when a user deliberately types --help, it's a legitimate, expected request, not an error. So help text should go to stdout (normal output) and return 0 (success); only misuse (like a missing argument) should go to stderr and return non-zero. Keeping the two apart matters — in a CI script, if ./tool --help unexpectedly returns non-zero it gets treated as a failure. Likewise, track toggle-style options with a flag variable (int verbose = 0): set it to 1 when you hit -v during the walk, then decide behavior from the flag afterward rather than acting mid-loop.",
